I think the empty docstring on `two_nsmul` is intentional and should not be removed, since the "sq" comment is irrelevant there.
That's bad practice. If you want to shut the `to_additive_doc` linter (which hasn't even been ported), you should tag with `nolint to_additive_doc`, not placate an empty docstring.
I misunderstood or misremembered how this worked; please disregard.
This file now also includes non-notation instances

Now in #10693
Did you intentionally remove those? If so, please update the commit message or PR title to reflect that
They were supposed to be removed in #9740. I'll mention in the PR description.
Can you split this removal to a new PR? I think this one is doing too many things.
Why did these move? I think they make sense where they were, and they certainly don't seem in scope for this PR.

`Algebra.Group.Pi` is a bag grab of imports while `Data.Pi.Algebra` is much more tame, and the instances I moved can be defined in it rather than being postponed for no good reason.
